---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'March 20, 2026';
---

<Layout>
	<main class="container">
		<div class="content">
			<div class="back-link">
				<a href="/coheria" class="back-btn">← Back to Coheria</a>
			</div>

			<div class="lang-switch">
				<a href="/coheria/privacy" class="lang-link">Version francaise</a>
			</div>

			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

			<p>
				Coheria is a mobile app dedicated to relaxation, guided breathing, and meditation.
				This policy fully discloses what data the app accesses, how it is used, and where it is stored.
			</p>

			<section>
				<h2>1. Summary</h2>
				<p>
					Coheria does not collect personal data on any server, does not sell data,
					and does not share data with third parties.
				</p>
				<p>
					The only data used by the app is technical preference data stored locally on your device
					to personalize your experience.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>2. Data Accessed and Collected</h2>
				<p>
					The following data may be stored locally by the app. It never leaves your device.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Selected session preference (session 1, 2, 3, or 4).</li>
					<li>Language preference.</li>
					<li>Display mode preference (theme).</li>
					<li>Audio preferences (on/off and in-app volume).</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					Sole purpose: remembering your settings for a better user experience.
				</p>
				<p>
					None of this data is used to identify, profile, or track you.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>3. Health Data</h2>
				<p>
					Coheria does not access or collect any Health Data.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>No access to Google Health Connect, Google Fit, Apple Health, or equivalent services.</li>
					<li>No reading or collection of medical, biometric, activity, or sleep data.</li>
					<li>No health-related inference from app usage.</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					The app does not rely on health data to provide its features.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>4. No Sharing or External Transmission</h2>
				<p>Coheria does not collect, store, or transmit to third parties:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Identity data (name, email, phone number, address).</li>
					<li>Health or medical data.</li>
					<li>Location data, contacts, or advertising identifiers.</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					No external API is used to process your preferences. No cloud sync is enabled.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>5. Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
				<p>
					Preferences remain stored locally while the app is installed.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Uninstalling the app removes associated local data.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>6. Security and Confidentiality</h2>
				<p>Because all data stays on your device:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>You keep full control over your information.</li>
					<li>Privacy is ensured by design (Privacy by Design).</li>
					<li>No server access exists to view your preferences.</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
				<p>
					Under GDPR, you have rights over your data. However, since no data is collected
					or processed outside your device, no external request is needed to exercise those rights.
				</p>
				<p>
					The publisher has no access to your preferences (session, language, display mode, audio),
					as they remain stored locally on your device.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>8. Changes</h2>
				<p>
					This policy may be updated to reflect technical or regulatory changes.
					Any update will be indicated in the application.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>9. Contact</h2>
				<p>
					For any question about this privacy policy, you can contact the publisher
					using the contact details shown on the app page.
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.container {
		min-height: 100vh;
		display: flex;
		justify-content: center;
		padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
	}

	.content {
		width: min(780px, 100%);
		animation: fadeInUp 0.5s ease-out;
	}

	@keyframes fadeInUp {
		from {
			opacity: 0;
			transform: translateY(20px);
		}
		to {
			opacity: 1;
			transform: translateY(0);
		}
	}

	.back-link {
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	.back-btn {
		color: #e5e5e5;
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		font-weight: 500;
	}

	.lang-switch {
		margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
	}

	.lang-link {
		font-size: 0.85rem;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);
		text-decoration: none;
		border-bottom: 1px solid transparent;
		transition: color 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.lang-link:hover {
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
		border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
	}

	h1 {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.5rem);
		line-height: 1.2;
	}

	.updated {
		margin-top: 0.65rem;
		color: #cccccc;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}

	p {
		color: #f2f2f2;
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	section {
		margin-top: 1.3rem;
		padding: 1rem 1.1rem;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
		border-radius: 12px;
	}

	h2 {
		margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
		font-size: 1.08rem;
		color: #ffffff;
	}

	ul {
		margin: 0.35rem 0 0;
		padding-left: 1.2rem;
	}

	li {
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
	}

	@media (max-width: 768px) {
		.container {
			padding: 1.25rem 1rem 2.25rem;
		}

		section {
			padding: 0.9rem;
		}
	}
</style>
